A wildlife park was forced to shut down after more than 300 manatees swam into the central pool at once.

The rush at Three Sisters Springs in Citrus County, Florida, came after a rise in tides at noon on Monday.

With an average of 65 manatees in the pool at once during cold weather, volunteers blocked off public walkways as they tried to ensure the animals' safety.

