Manatees are known to gravitate towards shallow springs during spells of low temperature in a bid to warm up.

Last week around 220 gathered in the pool.

But Monday's shift was a dramatic surge.

The park remains closed and wildlife officials will assess the situation at sunrise on Tuesday.

